column12: These might be better as FE but hard to define, you could leave as F
Indigo Bunting is difficult, might be better classified as a Forest Edge bird but can leave as Forest if you prefer
Desert species, open is probably better
We had these as forest but like indigo bunting they are difficult to assign. I now think they are best considered an open country species
Diurnal owl, changed from N to O
Waterbird changed from O to W
